  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. chronic systolic HF

          2. LVEF 35% or less, and a guideline-based class I or II indication for CRT 3) 3) They
             must be between 20 and 90 years old

        4) Predominantly in sinus rhythm 5) The GFR must be at least 45 cc/min if the patient is to
        receive gadolinium

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. inability to provide informed consent

          2. pregnancy

          3. presence of metal embedded in the body due to prior accident or injury, as documented
             by skull films or other imaging;

          4. cerebral aneurysm clips

          5. gadolinium contrast allergy (only if gadolinium is given)

          6. cochlear implants

          7. other metallic implants known to be contraindications to MRI

          8. severe claustrophobia

          9. acute kidney injury

         10. acute renal failure or chronic kidney disease with GFR &lt; 40 cc/min

         11. liver transplant

         12. gadolinium contrast allergy
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
